In the course is discussed the development of human geography in the past 60 years based on lectures, independent work with articles and a seminar. The topics are positivism, Marxism, humanism, structuralism, postmodernism, poststructuralism, poscolonialism and feminism in human geography.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course that students learn the development of theories in human geography in the last 60 years.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students * learn the development of theories in human geography in the last 60 years; * learn the concepts of ontology, epistemology, methodology and method and the use in different approaches in human geography; * learn principal geographers and their research in different approaches in human geography; * get familiar with important scientific artices of the theory of human geography and are able to discuss about them in seminar
